Welcome to the Portable North Pole!
This Customer Privacy Notice and Policy (“Privacy Policy”) is an important legal document which binds you and you should read it carefully before accessing our websites or purchasing, installing, accessing or using our products and services.
Introduction
This is the Privacy Policy of the Portable North Pole (“PNP”), which is a product and service offering of UGroupMédia Inc., a Canadian corporation (“UGM”).
The term “PNP”, except when it is used for description purposes, means UGM, and “we” and “our” and other such words refer to UGM. For definitions of other capitalized terms, please see the PNP Terms of Use and Terms of Sale. PNP Portable North Pole is a trademark of UGM. If you have any questions or concerns regarding the Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us.
Application of this Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy is for visitors and customers who access and use the internet websites listed below (“PNP Sites”), the PNP Mobile Apps (as defined below), or who use the services that are offered on the PNP Sites and the PNP Mobile Apps (the “PNP Services”) to create personalized digital content, including videos and calls, (“Content”) and includes an authorized link to this Privacy Policy. The term PNP Services includes your Submissions and Content for both PNP Sites and PNP Mobile Apps.
This Privacy Policy does not apply to any websites, products, or services, other than ours, nor to others’ websites linked in this Privacy Policy or in the PNP Sites or the PNP Services. We recommend that you examine the privacy statements posted on those other websites to understand their procedures for collecting, using, and disclosing Personal Information, as they may be different from ours. Examples of other sites include Facebook, X (Twitter), Instagram, Pinterest, YouTube, Stripe and PayPal.
Parts of this Privacy Policy also apply to Personal Information that you may provide to us when using our services or apps. In order to personalize our products and/or services, you may provide to us Personal Information of third parties (referred to here as “Third Party Personal Information”), for example the names, ages, photographs, video and audio recordings of your children, or details about other family members or friends. We may process the Third Party Personal Information if you provide us with this information for the purposes of the PNP Services. In this regard, you represent and warrant that you have obtained all necessary consents of the other people for all purposes described in this Privacy Policy for which we process Personal Information or have parental authority consistent with the full scope of rights granted to UGM pursuant to this Privacy Policy prior to providing us with their Personal Information.
Please see our
Terms of Use
for details of your responsibilities in relation to Third Party Personal Information.
We will only use Third Party Personal Information for the purpose of providing the personalized product or service you have requested. We will not use Third Party Personal Information for any other purpose. We treat Third Party Personal Information in the same way as your Personal Information, and will ensure that it benefits from the same level of protection.
This Privacy Policy applies to you if you visit any of our websites (our sites), or use any of our services or PNP mobile apps (generally referred to below as apps), or otherwise correspond with us by phone, email or otherwise.
Please note that your use of our websites and apps is also subject to our
