To customize your experience with the PNP Services
;
•
To better know and understand
the location, the age, and other characteristics of our clientele, as well as its needs, in order to improve our products and services. These analyses will be carried out using de-identified data organized into subgroups (strata).
•
To solicit information from you
, sometimes through surveys, to measure interest in and improve the PNP Services;
•
To enforce our
Terms of Use
,
Terms of Sale
and other agreements
;
•
To share or disclose Personal Information
to business analytics, customer service, marketing, distribution of surveys or sweepstakes programs, payment processors, cloud storage providers and fraud prevention firms; and
•
As otherwise described to you at the point of collection
.
To the extent permitted by law, we may create and share aggregate and anonymous information for use with third parties, including our advertisers and investors. For example, we may tell our advertisers the number of visitors the PNP Services receives or the most popular gifts or preferences. This data cannot be used to identify any individual and as such is not Personal Information.
OUR LEGAL BASIS FOR USING YOUR INFORMATION
We will only use your Personal Information when the law allows us to do so. Most commonly, we will use your Personal Information in the following circumstances:
•
Where you have given us your consent
. This is the case if you have confirmed that you have read and understood this notice and agree to the processing of your Personal Information for one or more specific purposes, such as receiving commercial communications.
•
Without your consent but according to one of the exceptions provided by applicable privacy laws
.
•
Where it is necessary in order to comply with a legal obligation
. This applies for example where we are required to retain your Personal Information for taxation reasons.
Depending on the purpose for which we are processing your Personal Information, we may rely on one or more of these legal basis.
