To business partners in conjunction with whom we may offer products or services
. If you choose to access these optional services, once we receive your consent, we may share information about you, including your Personal Information, with those partners.
•
To our affiliated entities and websites
. If you were referred to the PNP Sites from another website, we may share your registration information, such as your name, email address, mailing address, telephone number, and preferences about you with that referring website. We do not control the referring websites’ use of Personal Information, and we encourage you to review the privacy policies of any website that referred you to the PNP Sites. We may also share your Personal Information with any of our affiliated entities.
In addition to sharing your Personal Information as provided for above, we may also disclose your Personal Information in the following situations:
•
Business transfers by us
- in connection with a divestiture, merger, consolidation, asset sale, or other corporate transaction, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy.
•
When required by law
in response to subpoenas, court orders, or other legal process; to establish or exercise our legal rights; to defend against legal claims; or as otherwise required by law. In such cases, only necessary Personal Information will be disclosed.
•
When required to enforce our PNP
Terms of Use
, including situations when we believe it is necessary to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal or suspected illegal activities, or to protect and defend the rights, property, or safety of UGM and our affiliates, our customers, or others, and in connection with this Privacy Policy, our
Terms of Use
,
Terms of Sale
and other agreements.
5. Can your Personal Information be transferred to other jurisdictions?
Personal Information that we collect from you is directly processed and stored at, a destination outside the United Kingdom ("UK"), and may be processed, stored and transferred in Canada and in the United States ("US"). It may also be processed by staff operating elsewhere outside the UK who work for us or for one of our suppliers. Such staff maybe engaged in, among other things, the fulfilment of your order, the processing of your payment details and the provision of support services. Such transfer is necessary for the performance of our services.
Whenever we transfer your Personal Information that we collected from a third party in the UK outside of the UK, we will ensure a similar degree of protection is afforded to it by ensuring that at least one of the following safeguards is implemented:
• We will only transfer your Personal Information to countries that have been deemed to provide an adequate level of protection for Personal Information by the Secretary of State.
• We will only transfer your Personal Information to an organization that has agreed to comply with a framework for transfer of Personal Information recognized by the Secretary of State to provide an adequate level of protection for Personal Information.
• Where we use certain service providers, and in any other business relationship involving the transfer of your Personal Information outside the UK, we will use appropriate safeguards, such as standard contractual clauses approved by the Secretary of State which give Personal Information the same protection as in the UK. You may obtain such safeguards by contacting us using the contact details mentioned above.
We do not disclose your Personal Information unless we are satisfied that it will be adequately protected.
6. How do we protect your Personal Information?
The transmission of information by the internet is not secure and we cannot control or guarantee its security. Any transmission by you to us shall be at your own risk.
When you use our PNP Services and Content and send an email link or post on a forum, chat room or social network site, the Personal Information and content you share are visible to other users and may be viewed, collected or used by them. You are responsible for the Personal Information you chose to share or submit in these situations. Please take care when using these features. In this respect, it is your responsibility to ensure that you do not communicate sensitive Personal Information.
Once we have received your transmission, we will employ reasonable security procedures and practices appropriate to the nature of the information, to protect the Personal Information from unauthorized access, destruction, use, modification, or disclosure (a “Privacy Incident”). Our security measures are adapted to the quantity and sensitivity of Personal Information.
We restrict access to Personal Information only to those employees who need to have access to it in order to perform their duties.
We take reasonable steps to prevent Privacy Incidents. Any Privacy Incident, whether potential or actual, is taken seriously and will be communicated to the relevant supervisory authorities and individuals in accordance with privacy laws. Once we have received information from or about you, we will apply our security measures in an attempt to prevent any Privacy Incident.
Nevertheless, we cannot guarantee its security. In addition, it is important for you to protect against unauthorized access to your password and computer.
Please contact us if you have any questions regarding security or if you believe that your Personal Information has been compromised.
7. How long will we retain your Personal Information?
We will retain and delete your personalized call and video Content as provided in our
Terms of Sale
.
Last activity in your account
Subject to what is provided for in the
Terms of Sale
, we may retain your account registration information and Submissions for up to 26 months after your last activity in your account. Activity means that you access or use your PNP account for any purpose, including without limitation, logging into your account. This allows us to respond to any questions regarding previous account registrations or purchases, facilitate any future account registrations, purchases or renewals, comply with our accounting, tax and legal obligations, resolve disputes, enforce our agreements, prevent fraud, and is also for analytical purposes and record keeping integrity.
If you purchase or renew within the retention period for the video Content as provided for in the
Terms of Sale
, you will also have access to your video Content.
For free versions, after the expiration or termination of the free version, you will be able to access Submissions only, and not the video Content, as provided for in the
Terms of Sale
.
If your PNP account becomes inactive as referred to above, and after the 26-month period, we will disable your PNP account. When we disable your PNP account, your personalized Content will be deleted, but your Submissions and account registration information may remain in our archives for up to an additional 30 months for the reasons set forth above.
You may also receive email offers from us during the first 26-month period for our products and services unless you opt out as provided for in this Privacy Policy. You will be given the opportunity to opt out in every email we send to you, or alternatively, you can contact us using the contact details provided above.
Deletion of your PNP account
If you delete your PNP account as provided for in this Privacy Policy, your personalized Content and Submissions will be deleted, but your account registration information may remain in our archives for up to an additional 30 months for the reasons set forth above.
In addition, you may request, at any time, that we delete your Personal Information using this form
HERE
.
Additional storage in our archives
At the end of the additional 30 months, whether we disable your PNP account or you delete your PNP account, we reserve the right to retain in our archives certain Personal Information for up to 7 years as may be required for legal, regulatory, or other government compliance purposes. For example, we may keep information regarding your invoices which may include your email address, first and last name, language, country (IP address) and user ID, or your opt-in or opt-out status, or whether you deleted your PNP account yourself and if so, when.
Any Personal Information retained by PNP will be retained in accordance with this Privacy Policy and as may be applicable to the
Terms of Use
and
Terms of Sale
.
PNP reserves the right to delete your Personal Information, including any account information, Submissions and Content, as provided for in the
Terms of Sale
or
Terms of Use
. You are solely responsible for backing up any of this Personal Information.
8. How can you access and control your Personal Information and what choices do you have?
Under certain circumstances, you have the right, under applicable privacy laws, to:
•
Request access to your Personal Information
. This is commonly known as a ‘subject access request’ and enables you to receive a copy of the Personal Information we hold about you.
•
Request correction of the Personal Information that we hold about you
. This enables you to have any incomplete or inaccurate information we hold about you corrected.
•
Under certain circumstances, request erasure of your Personal Information
. This enables you to ask us to delete or remove Personal Information where there is no good reason for us continuing to process it. You also have the right to ask us to delete or remove your Personal Information in certain circumstances. Once we receive your request and confirm your identity, we will review your request to see if an exception allowing us to retain the information applies.
•
Under certain circumstances, request the restriction of processing of your Personal Information
. This enables you to ask us to suspend the processing of Personal Information about you, for example if you want us to establish its accuracy or the reason for processing it.
•
Request the transfer of your Personal Information to another party
and in a structured, commonly used technological format.
•
Withdraw consent
. If we are relying on your consent to process your Personal Information, you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time. Please note that, if you do withdraw your consent, you may not be able to benefit from our services. We will advise you if this is the case at the time you withdraw your consent.
•
Lodge a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority
. If you have any complaints about the way we process your Personal Information, please do contact us
HERE
.
•
Request additional information
, in a structured, commonly used technological format, about the processing of your Personal Information.
As set out above, we may use information held about you in order to notify you about our special offers and the products and services available from us. Your rights include the right to ask us not to process your Personal Information for these marketing purposes. You can exercise your right to prevent such processing by using the opt-out feature contained in all our marketing communications. You can also exercise the right at any time by contacting us
HERE
.
You may view, edit and delete much of your Personal Information online by accessing your account (you will be required to sign in using your password). If you would like to delete your account, from the “My account” section, select “delete account.” Once we receive your request to delete your account, all information, including Submissions and personalized Content related to your account, will be no longer available and will be deleted thereafter by us. When your PNP account data is deleted, it will be deleted from the active database, but certain Personal Information may remain in our archives for a specified period as set forth in this Privacy Policy and in the
Terms of Sale
.
If you make certain transactions (such as creating an account or purchasing Content or PNP Mobile Apps), we reserve the right to send you communications, including service announcements, administrative messages, and other non-promotional messages, without offering you the opportunity to opt out of receiving them. You can change your email at any time by logging into your account and going to the My Account page and amend your email notification choices.
If you wish, you can also opt out of receiving future promotional emails from us, you will have the opportunity to unsubscribe from future promotional messages by clicking the appropriate link at the bottom of  any such promotional email. When you opt out of promotional communications from us, you may still receive service messages (such as an order confirmation, content creation confirmation) and legally mandated notices.
ACCESS TO INFORMATION AND EXERCISING YOUR RIGHTS
You will not have to pay a fee to access your Personal Information, or exercise any of the other rights set out above. Please note that we may charge a reasonable fee if your request is clearly unfounded, repetitive or excessive. In certain circumstances, we may refuse to comply with your request.
In order to process your request, we may ask you for additional information to help us to confirm your identity, to ensure that your Personal Information is not disclosed to anyone who has no right to receive it. We will only use information you provide in your request for the purpose of verifying your identity or authority to make the request.
To exercise any of your rights you may reach us at the coordinates provides at the beginning of this Privacy Policy.
Only you, or someone legally authorized to act on your behalf, may make a request to know or delete related to your Personal Information. To designate an authorized agent, your agent will need to provide a Power of Attorney authorizing the agent to act on your behalf, or will need to complete the same verification procedures that would be required for a request submitted by you directly, and provide information that allows us to verify your authorization.
Describe your request with sufficient detail that allows us to properly understand, evaluate, and respond to it.
We cannot respond to your request or provide you with Personal Information if we cannot verify your identity or authority to make the request and confirm the personal information relates to you. We will only use Personal Information provided in the request to verify the requestor's identity or authority to make it.
We will confirm receipt of your request within seven (7) business days. If you do not receive confirmation within the 7-day timeframe, please resubmit your request by sending an email with the subject line “Privacy request unanswered” to
gdpr@ugroupmedia.com
or contact us at +1 514-871-3888.
We will aim to respond to your request within two (2) weeks. Sometimes it may take us longer than two weeks, if your request is complex or you have made a number of requests at the same time. If this is the case, we will notify you.
If you have an account with us associated with an email address, we will deliver our written response to that account email. If you do not have an account with us or an email address associated with your account, we will deliver our written response by mail or electronically, at your option.
For the transfer of your Personal Information to another party and in a structured, commonly used technological format, we will select a format to provide your personal information that is readily useable and should allow you to transmit the information from one entity to another entity without hindrance.
9. What Cookies and other web technologies do we use?
Our sites use cookies and other technologies to distinguish you from other users of our sites. This helps us to provide you with a good experience when you browse our sites and also allows us to improve our sites.
•
Cookies
. Cookies are small data text files that can be stored on your computer’s hard drive (if your web browser permits). We use cookies for the following general purposes:
•
To help us recognize your browser
. To help us recognize your browser as a previous visitor and save and remember any preferences that may have been set while your browser was visiting our PNP Site. For example, if you register on our PNP Site, we may use cookies to remember your registration information so you do not need to log into our PNP Site each time you visit. We also may record your password (PIN) in a cookie, if you checked the box entitled "Save this password (PIN) for automatic sign-in." Member IDs, passwords (PIN), and any other account-related data included in such cookies are encrypted for security purposes; and
•
To help us measure the PNP Sites’ effectiveness
. To help us measure the effectiveness of PNP Sites’ features and offerings, advertisements, and email communications by determining which emails you open and act upon.
•
For security
. We use cookies to detect fraud and abuse of our websites and services.
•
For social media
. Some of our websites include social media cookies, including those that enable users who are logged into social media service to share content via that service.
The “help” portion of the toolbar on most browsers should tell you how to prevent your browser from accepting new cookies, how to have the browser notify you when you receive a new cookie, or how to disable most types of cookies. However, if you refuse to accept cookies, you may not be able to access the PNP Sites, PNP Mobile Apps or PNP Services or many of the tools and features of the PNP Sites, PNP Mobile Apps or PNP Services.
•
Other web technologies
– web beacons. We also may use web beacons (also known as clear gifs, pixel tags or web bugs), which are tiny graphics with a unique identifier, similar in function to cookies, that are placed in the code of a web page. We use web beacons to monitor the traffic patterns of users from one page within our PNP Sites to another, to deliver or communicate with cookies, to understand whether you have come to our PNP Site from an online advertisement displayed on a third-party website, and to improve site performance. We also may allow our service providers to use web beacons to help us understand which emails have been opened by recipients and to track visitor traffic and actions on our PNP Site in order to measure the effectiveness of PNP Sites and other offerings.
From time to time, we may also allow, with your consent, certain third parties (such as Google Analytics) to collect information about your online activities through cookies and other technologies. The information gathered by these third parties is used for analytic purposes (i.e., to help us make predictions about your characteristics, interests or preferences and display advertisements on the PNP Sites tailored to your apparent interests).
Please note that we do not have access to or control over cookies or other technologies that these third parties may use to collect information about your interests other than through our websites, and the information practices of these third parties are not covered by this Privacy Policy. Some of these third parties may offer certain opt terms. Please note this does not opt you out of being served advertising. You will continue to receive generic ads.
Some browsers incorporate “Do Not Track” (DNT) features. We currently do not respond to DNT signals. There is not a common understanding of how to respond to DNT signals. In the meantime, we are trying to provide you a personalized service and ask that you use other tools such as ability to opt out of behavioral advertising as set forth above.
•
How Google uses data when you use our PNP Sites
. As noted below we may use Google Analytics and we want you to be aware of how Google may use your data when you use our PNP Sites and PNP Mobile Apps. Please see
https://www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/
.
If you would like to prevent your data from being used by Google Analytics, you can download and install the Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on for the Google Analytics JavaScript (ga.js, analytics.js, dc.js) at
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
.
Some of the cookies we use are essential for the operation of our sites. Also, some of the cookies may include, for example, cookies that enable you to log into areas of our sites or use a shopping cart. Except for such cookies, all cookies will expire after a period of 7 to 60 days.
Third-party cookies are retained for the period indicated in the relevant third-party privacy notice.
For more information, you can contact us
HERE
.
10. What about children’s online privacy protection?
We are committed to protecting the privacy needs of children, and we encourage parents and guardians to take an active role in their children’s online activities and interests.
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, any child under the age of 13 is considered a minor (a "Minor").
We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from Minors, and Minors are not permitted to provide any Personal Information to the PNP Sites or PNP Services. Anyone who is not considered a Minor is permitted to provide Personal Information (including Personal Information of Minors) to the PNP Sites and PNP Services subject to our
Terms of Use
and
Terms of Sale
. Minors may not in any way provide us with Personal Information. If we learn that we have collected Personal Information from a Minor, we will take steps to delete that information as soon as possible.
If you are a parent or guardian of a Minor, you have the right to request that we allow you to review, or delete, modify or stop further processing of your child’s Personal Information. If you wish to exercise these rights, please contact us at
gdpr@ugroupmedia.com
. We may ask you to authenticate your identity before complying with your requests.
Part of the Parental Access Rights, parents can access information of their Minor child's. If you believe your Minor child’s Personal Information is inadvertently collected or was collected without your consent, you may also request to know or delete content or information on behalf of your minor child by sending an email with the subject line “Minor Content Removal Request” to
gdpr@ugroupmedia.com
. Please specify in your request which website or application your request relates to and the specific information or content that you would like removed.
